---

description: Applies general Snakemake style guidelines
globs: \*_/_.smk

---

-   only use `shell` directive (ie, no `run`, etc)
-   `shell` should call CLI programs or a python script, eg: `python3 my_module.py --input 1 --flag`
-   bash in the `shell` should be structed for legibility
-   new lines + a tab before every CLI parameter, plus a pipe to the log eg:
    ```bash
    my tool \
        -p1 100 \
        -p2 200 \
        --flag \
    >2 {log} 2>&1
    ```
-   every rule should (generally) have
    -   input
    -   output
    -   shell
    -   log
    -   (conda, depending)
-   each rule should be fairly well-contained and do a single task, eg:
    -   flye assemble genome
    -   filter reads
-   use general best practices
